Larry Hagman, whose role as oil-predator magnate J. A. Ewing in the Dallas TV series became a symbol of greed in the 1980s, has died.
He was 81 years old.
Hagman, who returned this year as J.R. in the new Dallas season, died Friday evening from complications caused by cancer, according to a family statement provided to The Associated Press by Warner Bros., the Dallas production studio.
